# Rules for Web Payment Gateway (Stripe)

## 1. Stripe Checkout Integration
- Do not build custom credit card input forms. Utilize Stripe Checkout for maximum PCI compliance and conversion rate.
- On the Pricing Page, clicking "Upgrade to Pro" must POST to the backend checkout endpoint, retrieve the `sessionId`, and use `@stripe/stripe-js` `redirectToCheckout({ sessionId })`.

## 2. Customer Management (Invoices)
- Inside the User Settings view, provide a "Manage Billing & Invoices" button.
- This button must redirect the user to the Stripe Customer Portal (retrieved via the backend portal endpoint) allowing them to download tax invoices, update cards, or cancel securely.